    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="Kali150-kilavi">itu poruḷvayiṟ pirinta talaivaṉai 1niṉaittu āṟṟāta talaiviyait tōḻi āṟṟuvittatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en"></p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="Kali150">
              <l>alarntikaḻ naṟuṅkoṉṟai yalaṅkalan teriyalā</l>
              <l>ṉilaṅkeyi leyappiṟanta veripōla vevvāyuṅ</l>
              <l>kaṉaikatir teṟutaliṟ kaṭutteḻunta kāmputtī </l>
              <l>malaiparantu talaikkoṇṭu muḻaṅkiya muḻaṅkaḻaṉ</l>
              <l>mayaṅkatar maṟukaliṉ malaitalaik koṇṭeṉa</l>
              <l>vicumpuṟa nivantaḻalum vilaṅkaru veñcuram;</l>
              <l rend="space">iṟantutā meṇṇiya veytutal vēṭkaiyā</l>
              <l>laṟantuṟan tāyiḻā yākkattiṟ pirintavar</l>
              <l>piṟaṅkunīr caṭaikkarantā ṉaṇiyaṉṉa niṉṉiṟam</l>
              <l>pacantunī yiṉaiyaiyāy nīkkalu nīppavō;</l>
              <l rend="space">karikāynta kavalaittāyk kalkāynta kāṭṭakam</l>
              <l>veruvanta vāṟeṉṉār viḻupporuṭ kakaṉṟava</l>
              <l>ruruvavēṟ ṟūrtiyā ṉoḷḷaṇinak kaṉṉaniṉ  </l>
              <l>ṉuruviḻan tiṉaiyaiyā yuḷḷalu muḷḷupavō;</l>
              <l rend="space">kotitturāyk kuṉṟivarntu koṭikkoṇṭa kōṭaiyā</l>
              <l>lotukkariya neṟiyeṉṉā roṇporuṭ kakaṉṟavar</l>
              <l>pututtiṅkaṭ kaṇṇiyāṉ poṟpūṇñāṉ ṟaṉṉaniṉ</l>
              <l>katuppulaṟuṅ kaviṉaiyāyk kāṇṭaluṅ kāṇpavō;</l>
              <l rend="space">āṅku,</l>
              <l>arumpeṟa lātiraiyā ṉaṇipeṟa malarnta</l>
              <l>peruntaṇ caṇpakam pōla voruṅkavar</l>
              <l>poyyā rākuta ṟeḷintaṉa</l>
              <l>maiyī rōti maṭamoḻi yōyē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
              <l>The fire of bamboo shafts that rose throbbingly because of the scorching of intense [sun] rays</l>
              <l>everywhere like the flame that was born when the one with a swaying pretty garland </l>
              <l>of  blooming bright laburnum shot at the shining fortresses,</l>
              <l>because the wildly roaring  fire, having spread over the mountain [and] expanding,</l>
              <l>whirl across the confused paths, because it expands over the mountain,</l>
              <l corresp="1-6">comes up so as to reach the sky [and] burns the transverse hot desert difficult [to cross].</l>
              <l>Will he who separated [from you] for gain, you with choice jewels, abandoning dharma</l>
              <l>out of a desire to cross [and] reach the things he thinks of</l>
              <l>forsake you, as you are like this, having paled in your complexion </l>
              <l corresp="7-10">that was like the decorations of the one who matted hair the glistening water is hidden?</l>
              <l>Will he who departed for excellent wealth, one who does not say the way are frightening </l>
              <l>inside the wilderness where the stones are hot, having become distress that burns the witnesses, </l>
              <l>think of you as you are like this, having lost you form (beauty/colour?)</l>
              <l corresp="11-14">that was like the bright ornaments of one whose vehicle is a shapely bull?</l>
              <l>The one who departed for bright wealth, one who does not say the paths are difficult to walk</l>
              <l>because of the west wind/summer sun(?) that has taken the creepers, boiling, moving on, rising on the hills,</l>
              <l>will he see [you] being one whose beauty has dried up, with your hair</l>
              <l corresp="15-18">that hung down like the golden ornament of the one with the new moon in [his] chaplet?</l>
              <l corresp="19">Thus,</l>
              <l>like the big cool Campaka [flower]</l>
              <l>that blooms so that the one from Ardra difficult to obtain get it as decoration</l>
              <l>it has become clear to us that he does not lie at all,</l>
              <l corresp="20-23">oh you with innocent words [and] black [oil-]moist hair.</l>
            </lg>
